# Important Breaking Change: Prefill Removed in Opus 4.6

**Prefill is no longer supported in Opus 4.6.** If you send a request with an assistant message prefix, you'll get a **400 error**. You need to migrate before upgrading.

## Migration Path: Use Structured Outputs

The recommended replacement is **structured outputs**, which guarantee format compliance without prefilling:

```python
# OLD (will break on Opus 4.6)
messages=[
    {"role": "user", "content": "Generate a report"},
    {"role": "assistant", "content": "# Report\n"}  # ❌ Prefill
]

# NEW (Opus 4.6 compatible)
messages=[
    {"role": "user", "content": "Generate a report"}
]
output_config={
    "type": "text",
    "format": {
        "type": "json_schema",
        "schema": {
            "type": "object",
            "properties": {
                "title": {"type": "string"},
                "sections": {
                    "type": "array",
                    "items": {
                        "type": "object",
                        "properties": {
                            "heading": {"type": "string"},
                            "content": {"type": "string"}
                        },
                        "required": ["heading", "content"]
                    }
                }
            },
            "required": ["title", "sections"]
        }
    }
}
```

## Why This Is Better

- **Guaranteed format** — JSON schema enforcement, not heuristic-based
- **More efficient** — No token waste on example prefixes
- **Works with all features** — Compatible with streaming, caching, thinking
- **Easier to parse** — Structured outputs are validated before returning

