# Streaming with Tool Use: A Clear Guide

You're asking the right question—streaming + tool use requires some coordination. Here's how it works:

## The Core Mechanics

**Streaming shows you:**
1. Claude's thinking/reasoning in real-time (text deltas)
2. **Tool call parameters as they're generated** (fine-grained tool streaming, GA)
3. Text after tool results
4. **NOT** the tool execution itself (that's synchronous on your end)

**Key point:** Streaming doesn't make tool execution itself faster—Claude still waits for results before continuing. But you *see* what's happening in real-time, and tool parameters stream in as they're built.

## Basic Implementation Pattern

Here's how to handle it:

```typescript
const stream = client.messages.stream({
  model: "claude-opus-4-5-sonnet",
  max_tokens: 4096,
  stream: true,  // Enable streaming
  tools: [
    {
      type: "builtin",
      name: "web_search_20260209",
    },
    {
      type: "builtin",
      name: "code_execution_20260120",
    }
  ],
  messages: [
    { role: "user", content: "Search for Claude pricing and run a Python script to calculate annual cost" }
  ],
});

// Process events in real-time
stream.on("contentBlockStart", (event) => {
  if (event.content_block.type === "tool_use") {
    console.log(`📍 Starting tool call: ${event.content_block.name}`);
  } else if (event.content_block.type === "text") {
    console.log("💬 Text block starting...");
  }
});

stream.on("contentBlockDelta", (event) => {
  // Text streaming
  if (event.delta.type === "text_delta") {
    process.stdout.write(event.delta.text);
  }

  // Tool parameter streaming (fine-grained)
  if (event.delta.type === "input_json_delta") {
    console.log(`  [param] ${event.delta.partial_json}`);
  }
});

stream.on("contentBlockStop", (event) => {
  console.log("\n");
});

stream.on("messageStop", async (event) => {
  // When message is done, check if we need to handle tool calls
  const response = event.message;

  if (response.stop_reason === "tool_use") {
    // Tool calls have been streamed - now you execute them
    const toolUseBlocks = response.content.filter(
      (block) => block.type === "tool_use"
    );

    for (const toolCall of toolUseBlocks) {
      const result = await executeTool(toolCall.name, toolCall.input);
      console.log(`✅ ${toolCall.name} result:`, result);

      // Feed result back for next message
      // (see below for continuation pattern)
    }
  } else if (response.stop_reason === "end_turn") {
    console.log("✨ Claude finished responding");
  }
});
```

## The Tool Use Loop: Handling Multiple Rounds

When Claude calls tools, you must execute them and send results back. Here's the full flow:

```typescript
async function chatWithTools(userMessage: string) {
  const messages: MessageParam[] = [
    { role: "user", content: userMessage }
  ];

  let continueLoop = true;

  while (continueLoop) {
    const stream = client.messages.stream({
      model: "claude-opus-4-5-sonnet",
      max_tokens: 4096,
      stream: true,
      tools: [
        { type: "builtin", name: "web_search_20260209" },
        { type: "builtin", name: "code_execution_20260120" }
      ],
      messages,
    });

    // Stream and collect the response
    const response = await stream.finalMessage();

    // Process based on stop reason
    if (response.stop_reason === "tool_use") {
      // Extract tool calls from streamed response
      const toolCalls = response.content.filter(
        (block): block is ToolUseBlock => block.type === "tool_use"
      );

      // Add Claude's message (with tool calls) to history
      messages.push({ role: "assistant", content: response.content });

      // Execute tools and collect results
      const toolResults: ToolResultBlockParam[] = [];

      for (const toolCall of toolCalls) {
        try {
          const result = await executeTool(toolCall.name, toolCall.input);
          toolResults.push({
            type: "tool_result",
            tool_use_id: toolCall.id,
            content: JSON.stringify(result),
          });
        } catch (error) {
          toolResults.push({
            type: "tool_result",
            tool_use_id: toolCall.id,
            is_error: true,
            content: `Error: ${error.message}`,
          });
        }
      }

      // Send tool results back
      messages.push({ role: "user", content: toolResults });
    } else {
      // Claude finished (end_turn or stop)
      continueLoop = false;
      console.log("Final response:", response.content);
    }
  }
}

